ZH: 他们经常取笑我笨拙的动作。
EN: They often make fun of my clumsiness.

ZH: 不要取笑别人的梦想，虽然它们很不现实。
EN: Don't mock others' dreams, even if they seem unrealistic.

ZH: 如果你取笑别人，对方可能会感到受伤。
EN: If you ridicule someone, they may feel hurt.

ZH: 他们取笑了我的穿着，在我不在场的时候。
EN: They laughed at my outfit when I wasn't around.

ZH: 她的同学常常取笑她过于认真。
EN: Her classmates often tease her for being too serious.

ZH: 我们之间的互相取笑气氛总是很轻松。
EN: The teasing atmosphere between us is always relaxed.

ZH: 请不要取笑我的口音，我正在努力学习。
EN: Please don't make fun of my accent, I'm trying to learn.

ZH: 在一个友好的气氛中取笑朋友是可以接受的。
EN: It's acceptable to tease friends in a friendly atmosphere.

ZH: 这样取笑别人是不尊重的行为。
EN: It's disrespectful to mock others like that.

ZH: 我们只是取笑他的新发型，没有恶意。
EN: We were just teasing him about his new hairstyle, no harm intended.

ZH: 没有人喜欢被取笑，即使是开玩笑。
EN: Nobody likes to be laughed at, even if it's meant as a joke.

ZH: 孩子们应该学会不取笑别人的外貌。
EN: Children should learn not to make fun of others' appearances.

ZH: 我们的友谊允许我们相互取笑。
EN: Our friendship allows us to tease each other.

ZH: 我们的团队经常取笑彼此，但我们之间关系很好。
EN: Our team often jokes around with each other, but we have a good relationship.

ZH: 不要取笑别人站错队，每个人都会犯错。
EN: Don't mock others for standing in the wrong line, everyone makes mistakes.

ZH: 在一些文化中，取笑是传统的友好方式。
EN: In some cultures, teasing is a traditional friendly way of communication.

ZH: 她对我们犯错的时候不取笑，总是鼓励我们。
EN: She never ridicules us when we make mistakes, always encourages us.

ZH: 取笑长辈是不礼貌的行为。
EN: It's impolite to make fun of elders.

ZH: 他受够了被取笑的感觉，所以决定辞职。
EN: He was fed up with being laughed at, so he decided to quit.

ZH: 虽然他被取笑过，但是他不会放弃自己的梦想。
EN: Despite being mocked, he won't give up on his dreams.
